row.cell:
(Chile’s oldest party, traditionally represented Chile’s middle class;
                            after several schisms, became a “revolutionary” party. Recently merged
                            with the Social Democrats, a mini-party of similar bent)

div.p:
(1) The United Popular Action Movement (MAPU),
                    a radical Christian Democratic Party splinter which is part of the UP. Most of MAPU’s more prominent members deserted to the Christian Left Party
                    after it was formed last year;
